@database 49736_Taglines.guide

@node Main "49736_Taglines Documentation"

                       49736_Taglines
 Forty nine thousand, seven hundred and thirty six new taglines.

                  Compiled by Glen Shannon
                     13th January 1998

Introduction:
-------------

Guess what ?  It's 49736 taglines for YAM2.  These taglines were
unashamedly ripped from all of the comm/cnet/supertag#?.lha archives
on Aminet.



Installation:
-------------

You can install the taglines from the directory where this guide
resides, no matter where it is.

Click @{"here" system "execute Install"} or double-click on the Install icon.
You will be given 3 choices:

1)  Join the 49736_taglines file onto the existing YAM:.taglines file.
2)  Replace the YAM:.taglines file with this file.
3)  Quit the installation.

This is my first attempt at writing an installer.  Since I couldn't be
bothered learning how to write a Commodore Installer script, I wrote it
in AmigaDOS.  It seems to work well enough.  A backup of your current
YAM:.taglines file is made (YAM:.taglines.backup) if you decide to
install, otherwise it is left alone.  Provision is also made in case you
have an existing YAM:.taglines.backup file.


Copyright:
----------

This archive is not copyrighted in any way.  If however, you want to use
my installation script (modified or not modified), I'd appreciate it if
you left my name in there.

The original comm/cnet/supertag from Aminet contained no form of copyright
message, therefore it is was completely legal and okay for me to have made
this file.

How can you copyright a tagline anyway ???
@endnode
